sentences: By age 16 (1991), he began performing at music clubs with his initial band Mr. No.
In 1994, he was invited to join Kargo as the keyboard player by Selim Ozturk and Mehmet Senol Sisli.
In 1995, Mr. No won the best group award given annually by RockHouse.
In 1996, Kargo released their debut-album “Yarina Ne Kaldi?
Kargo released their second album “Sevmek Zor” (Love Is Hard) in 1997.
Also in 1997, Çeliköz began working with other artists as he did the keyboard and synthesizer arrangements for Athena, Turkish Ska band.
He released 3 more albums with Kargo during 1998–2000, Yalnizlik Mevsimi (Season of Loneliness), Sen Bir Meleksin (You are an angel) and Best of Kargo.
In 2000, Çeliköz with his bandmate Selim Ozturk take the lead in directing and guiding Asli, Turkish Rock Singer, through her first solo album “Neresindeyim”.
His collaboration with Asli still continues to date as he has produced her second and third albums “Su Gibi” in 2004 and “Dans Etmeye Ihtiyacim Var” in 2007.
His collaboration with Asli still continues to date as he has produced her second and third albums “Su Gibi” in 2004 and “Dans Etmeye Ihtiyacim Var” in 2007.
In 2001, Çeliköz returned working with his initial rock band Mr. No, this time as a record producer.
During 2002 he worked with Teoman, a widely popular Turkish acoustic rock singer and songwriter, on two projects as an arranger.
After a three-year hiatus, Kargo regrouped in 2003 to begin work on their next studio album.
In 2004, Çeliköz also played keyboards in debut album of Yalın, Turkish pop singer.
In 2006, Çeliköz produced Yalın’s second album “Bir Bakmissin” which received favorable critiques and high sales numbers.
In 2007, Çeliköz released “Yildizlarin Altinda” (Under the Stars) with Kargo.
“Gulmeyi Dene” is planned to be released in May 2008.
He started writing music for commercials first for Kargo’s 2000 commercial for Efes Dark, a product of Efes Beverage Group.
Most recent commercial work of Çeliköz, as a member of JinglePeople is for Jacobs Coffee released in 2008.
Towards the end of 2008, Serkan Çeliköz and Koray Candemir decided to end their involvement with Kargo due to vision and opinion differences with the other members.
Together they formed their new band 'maSKott' and are currently living in Seattle while working on new projects between tour dates to promote their new album Tuval.
(What Is Left For Tomorrow?)
Later on that year Celikoz left Mr. No due to his heavy touring schedule with Kargo.
Their 2004 release “Ates ve Su” (Fire and Water) was welcomed by the fans with great interest.
Yalın’s album “Ellerine Saglik” sold 200,000 copies within first week and reached 500,000 copies at the end of 4 months.
Çeliköz has recently finished working on debut solo album for Cenkhan, Turkish Rock Singer, as a producer and arranger for keyboards and synthesizer.
